Description: Typical range for 1064 nm fiber lasers in wood cleaning to balance efficiency and avoid charring; starting at 150 W for willow's low thermal conductivity (~0.15 W/mK) prevents substrate damage. Source: IPG Photonics YLR series specs and studies on laser wood surface treatment (e.g., Journal of Cultural Heritage, 2018).

Optimal scanning speed for efficient area coverage and effective cleaning
Optimal number of passes for complete cleaning without excessive processing
Beam overlap percentage for uniform cleaning coverage
